{# ============================================================
   Recipe-Rewriting Prompt Template
   Course: Advanced NLP (SoSe 2026) — Homework 2, Part 5
   ============================================================
   Expected input variables:
     - recipe:  { title, cuisine, servings, ingredients[], steps[] }
     - user:    { name, skill_level, restrictions[], allergies[], output_format }
     - options: { include_nutrition, include_shopping_list, include_hints,
                  num_variants }
============================================================ #}

{# ----- reusable bullet-list macro ----- #}
{%- macro bullet_list(items, marker='-') -%}
{% for item in items %}{{ marker }} {{ item }}
{% endfor %}
{%- endmacro -%}

You are an expert chef and nutrition coach. Your task is to **rewrite the
recipe below** so it perfectly fits the user's profile.

============================================================
USER PROFILE
============================================================
Name:         {{ user.name }}
Skill level:  {{ user.skill_level | upper }}
{% if user.restrictions -%}
Dietary restrictions ({{ user.restrictions | length }}):
{{ bullet_list(user.restrictions) -}}
{%- else -%}
Dietary restrictions: none
{% endif %}
{% if user.allergies -%}
Allergies (MUST be avoided):
{{ bullet_list(user.allergies, marker='!') -}}
{%- else -%}
Allergies: none reported
{% endif %}
Preferred output format: {{ user.output_format }}

============================================================
ORIGINAL RECIPE
============================================================
Title:    {{ recipe.title }}
Cuisine:  {{ recipe.cuisine }}
Servings: {{ recipe.servings }}

Ingredients ({{ recipe.ingredients | length }}):
{{ bullet_list(recipe.ingredients) }}
Original steps:
{% for step in recipe.steps %}{{ loop.index }}. {{ step }}
{% endfor %}
============================================================
REWRITE INSTRUCTIONS
============================================================
1. Replace any ingredient that conflicts with the user's restrictions or
   allergies. For every substitution, briefly explain *why* it was made.
2. Adapt the level of detail to the user's skill level:
{% if user.skill_level == 'beginner' %}
   - The user is a BEGINNER: explain each technique (e.g. "fold", "deglaze"),
     give approximate times, and add safety reminders.
{% elif user.skill_level == 'intermediate' %}
   - The user is INTERMEDIATE: keep instructions concise but include any
     non-obvious technique tips.
{% else %}
   - The user is ADVANCED: keep it terse; assume standard culinary vocabulary.
{% endif %}
3. Present the rewritten recipe in **{{ user.output_format }}** format:
{% if user.output_format == 'numbered' %}
   - Use a numbered list (1., 2., 3., ...).
{% elif user.output_format == 'bulleted' %}
   - Use bullet points (-).
{% elif user.output_format == 'paragraph' %}
   - Write a single flowing paragraph, no lists.
{% endif %}
{% if options.include_hints %}
4. Add a short "Chef's hints" section with 2-3 practical tips
   (e.g. how to tell when the dish is done, common mistakes to avoid).
{% endif %}
{% if options.include_nutrition %}
5. Add an "Estimated nutrition (per serving)" section with calories,
   protein (g), carbs (g), fat (g). Mark the values as approximate.
{% endif %}
{% if options.include_shopping_list %}
6. Add a "Shopping list" section at the end, grouped by store aisle
   (produce, dairy/alternatives, dry goods, ...).
{% endif %}

{% if options.num_variants and options.num_variants > 1 -%}
============================================================
ADDITIONAL VARIANTS REQUESTED: {{ options.num_variants }}
============================================================
After the main rewrite, produce {{ options.num_variants - 1 }} additional
variant(s) of the dish that still respect the user's restrictions:
{% for i in range(options.num_variants - 1) -%}
- Variant {{ i + 1 }}: change ONE major component (protein, sauce, or starch).
{% endfor %}
{%- endif %}

============================================================
OUTPUT
============================================================
Return your answer in clearly labelled sections. Do not include any text
outside the labelled sections.
